Package camzup.core

Class MeshEntity2

java.lang.Object
camzup.core.Entity
camzup.core.Entity2
camzup.core.MeshEntity2
All Implemented Interfaces:
IEntity, ISpatial2, ISvgWritable, IUtils, IVolume, IVolume2, java.lang.Iterable<Mesh2>
public class MeshEntity2
extends Entity2
implements java.lang.Iterable<Mesh2>, IVolume2, ISvgWritable
An entity which contains a transform that is applied to a list of meshes. The meshes may references a list of materials by index.

    • toBlenderCode

      public java.lang.String toBlenderCode()
      Returns a String of Python code targeted toward the Blender 2.8x API. This code is brittle and is used for internal testing purposes, i.e., to compare how curve geometry looks in Blender (the control) versus in the library (the test).
      Returns:
      the string

    • toBlenderCode

      public java.lang.String toBlenderCode​(MaterialSolid[] materials, float gamma, float metallic, float roughness, float specular, float clearcoat, float clearcoatRough, float extrude, float offset)
      Returns a String of Python code targeted toward the Blender 2.8x API. This code is brittle and is used for internal testing purposes, i.e., to compare how mesh geometry looks in Blender (the control) versus in the library (the test).
      Parameters:
      materials - the materials
      gamma - color adjustment
      metallic - metallic factor
      roughness - roughness factor
      specular - specular highlight strength
      clearcoat - clear coat factor
      clearcoatRough - clear coat roughness
      extrude - extrude the shape
      offset - extrusion offset
      Returns:
      the string

    • toSvgElm

      public java.lang.String toSvgElm​(java.lang.String id, float zoom, MaterialSolid[] materials)
      Creates a string representing a group node in the SVG format. This SVG is designed for compatibility with Processing, not for efficiency.

      Stroke weight is impacted by scaling in transforms, so zoom is a parameter. If nonuniform zooming is used, zoom can be an average of width and height or the maximum dimension.
      Parameters:
      id - the face id prefix
      zoom - scaling from external transforms
      materials - the materials to use
      Returns:
      the string

    • contains

      public static boolean contains​(MeshEntity2 me, Vec2 pointGlobal, Vec2 pointLocal)
      Evaluates whether the mesh entity contains a point. Multiplies the global point by the transform's inverse to produce the point in local space.
      Parameters:

      pointGlobal - the point in global space
